{"id":1479,"date":"2022-10-24T18:53:58","date_gmt":"2022-10-24T18:53:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1479"},"modified":"2022-11-27T12:04:28","modified_gmt":"2022-11-27T12:04:28","slug":"customizing-linux-terminal","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1479","title":{"rendered":"Customizing Linux Terminal"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>I just wanted to show you what kind of terminal I&#8217;m using and it&#8217;s advantages in real world use.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Installing Terminator<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step would be installing in what&#8217;s my opinion the best terminal emulator. It uses appearance settings, hotkeys, text search, arrange terminals. IT has many interesting and good-looking themes, which is also very important because you&#8217;ll be looking at the thing for many many hours.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on the distro use<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>sudo apt-get install terminator -y<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>sudo dnf install terminator -y<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"777\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?resize=640%2C777&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1480\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?w=656&amp;ssl=1 656w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?resize=247%2C300&amp;ssl=1 247w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?resize=20%2C24&amp;ssl=1 20w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?resize=30%2C36&amp;ssl=1 30w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image.png?resize=40%2C48&amp;ssl=1 40w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h3>Installing Zsh<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As a default, you are probably using bash which is is a rewrite of the old Bourne shell (<em>sh<\/em>) that shipped in UNIX. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Zsh&nbsp;is intended to be friendlier than bash, through better interaction. Some of its useful features are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Programmable command line completion<\/li><li>Shared command history between running shell sessions<\/li><li>Spelling correction<\/li><li>Loadable modules<\/li><li>Interactive selection of files and folders<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo dnf install zsh -y<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>To start using it type &#8220;zsh&#8221; into the terminal and you should see similar output to this<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"470\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?resize=640%2C470&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1481\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?w=663&amp;ssl=1 663w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?resize=300%2C220&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?resize=36%2C26&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-1.png?resize=48%2C35&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s leave everything  in default for now, so simply type 0.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Set Zsh as the default shell<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that type<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>chsh -s $(which zsh)<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you had any custom ~\/.bashrc settings or aliaes dont forget to move them to ~\/.zshrc<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Installing Oh my Zsh<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u00a0Oh my zsh is an open source, community-driven framework for managing your Zsh configuration. It comes bundled with thousands of helpful functions, helpers, plugins, themes etc.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To install it we use simple script provided by their github<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sh -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/robbyrussell\/oh-my-zsh\/master\/tools\/install.sh)\"\r<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"247\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=640%2C247&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1483\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?w=993&amp;ssl=1 993w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=300%2C116&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=768%2C296&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-2.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type yes and you are good to go.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=640%2C200&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1484\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?w=988&amp;ssl=1 988w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=300%2C94&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=768%2C239&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-3.png?resize=48%2C15&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Changing a theme, background, fonts etc.<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Right click on the terminator and choose &#8220;Preferences&#8221;. Now to into the Colors>Foreground and Background and go into the drop down menu. My theme of choice is &#8220;Solarized dark&#8221; and again &#8220;Solarized&#8221; for the Palette.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"456\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=640%2C456&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1485\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=1024%2C730&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=300%2C214&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=768%2C548&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=24%2C17&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=36%2C26&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?resize=48%2C34&amp;ssl=1 48w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-4.png?w=1084&amp;ssl=1 1084w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the fonts we are going to use a package called &#8220;Powerline-fonts&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple use package manager to download it, but from my experience with this package, different distros have different package names, so watch out.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo dnf install powerline powerline-fonts -y<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"change-theme-to-agnoster\">Change theme to Agnoster<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>You need to change\u00a0<code>ZSH_THEME=\"robbyrussell\"<\/code>\u00a0to\u00a0<code>ZSH_THEME=\"agnoster\"<\/code>\u00a0in your .zshrc<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"252\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?resize=640%2C252&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1488\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?w=657&amp;ssl=1 657w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?resize=300%2C118&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?resize=36%2C14&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/image-6.png?resize=48%2C19&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Restart your terminal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Plugins<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The great feature of ZFS is that you can add many more features in form of plugins. I&#8217;m gonna show you a few of my favorite ones<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"autosuggestions\">Autosuggestions<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>Autosuggestion work using your zsh history. This greatly increases your typing speed. https:\/\/github.com\/zsh-users\/zsh-autosuggestions<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>git clone https:\/\/github.com\/zsh-users\/zsh-autosuggestions ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~\/.oh-my-zsh\/custom}\/plugins\/zsh-autosuggestions<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Add the plugin to the list of plugins for Oh My Zsh to load (inside ~\/.zshrc):\u00a0<code>plugins=(zsh-autosuggestions)<\/code><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"syntax-highlighting\">Syntax highlighting<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>git clone https:\/\/github.com\/zsh-users\/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>echo \"source ${(q-)PWD}\/zsh-syntax-highlighting\/zsh-syntax-highlighting.zsh\" >> ${ZDOTDIR:-$HOME}\/.zshrc<a href=\"https:\/\/maxim-danilov.github.io\/make-linux-terminal-great-again\/#syntax-highlighting\"><\/a><\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 id=\"remove-hostname\">Remove hostname<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>This is not really a plugin, but I like the clean look of it, therefore we\u2019ll remove this. Add this line to end of your ~\/.zshrc<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>prompt_context() {} <\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/maxim-danilov.github.io\/make-linux-terminal-great-again\/#syntax-highlighting\"><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I just wanted to show you what kind of terminal I&#8217;m using and it&#8217;s advantages [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1493,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[208],"tags":[511],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/terminator_zsh.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1479"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=1479"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1479\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1492,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1479\/revisions\/1492"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/1493"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=1479"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=1479"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=1479"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}